Preconditions:
The method mergeAlternately should take two string parameters, word1 and wordThe strings word1 and word2 should not be null.

Postconditions:
The method should return a string that is the merged result of word1 and wordThe merged string should contain the characters from word1 and word2 alternately.
If word1 is longer than word2, the remaining characters of word1 should be appended to the end of the merged string.
If word2 is longer than word1, the remaining characters of word2 should be appended to the end of the merged string.
The order of the characters in the merged string should be maintained as per the original order of word1 and word2.